personalities.name: Deepa Maisuria
personalities.description: The primary organizer, she initiates the group, sets the itinerary, clarifies details, and ensures everyone's needs (especially the kids') are considered.

personalities.name: ashish garg
personalities.description: He's the practical one, asking logistical questions about check-ins and passes, handling room assignments, and then casually offering 'gummies' for the evening's entertainment.

personalities.name: Raveen Bhalla
personalities.description: Reliable and detail-oriented, he confirms information, monitors external factors like air quality, and is ready to jump in to help with logistics or wrangle kids for naps.

personalities.name: Sonia Delhon
personalities.description: Brimming with enthusiasm, she researches and suggests activities, provides useful information (like pool prices), and is always excited about shared meals and fun.

personalities.name: Jennifer Jolly
personalities.description: She's spontaneous and flexible, ready to coordinate travel, bring games, shift plans on a dime, and is always eager for a social gathering or a dip in the hot tub.

personalities.name: Shawn Kanungo
personalities.description: The group's resident jokester, he lightens the mood with witty remarks, uses emojis, and is consistently focused on finding the next social event or 'after after party'.

personalities.name: Jeff Leong
personalities.description: He's keen on active pursuits, asking about hotel amenities like pools and consistently extending open invitations for hikes, embracing the mountain environment.

personalities.name: Tessa Leong
personalities.description: A supportive co-pilot, she coordinates effortlessly with her partner, asks practical questions for the group's comfort, and is quick to offer assistance with food runs or kids' needs.

personalities.name: Nazia Shaikh
personalities.description: She's an active participant by presence, absorbing all the group's plans and chatter without feeling the need to contribute verbally.

personalities.name: Fahad Shaikh
personalities.description: A true mystery, his complete silence in the chat makes him the ultimate observer, possibly enjoying the trip without any digital footprint.

red_flags.name: Deepa Maisuria
red_flags.description: Her initial date mix-up and subsequent detailed corrections show a slight overreliance on her own organizational prowess, sometimes leading to minor confusion.

red_flags.name: ashish garg
red_flags.description: His casual offer of 'gummies' for the after-party highlights a playful disregard for the 'family trip' vibe, perhaps pushing the boundaries of what's appropriate for a group with kids.

red_flags.name: Raveen Bhalla
red_flags.description: His intense focus on air quality and detailed logistical confirmations suggests he might be a bit of an information-overloader, always needing to verify every detail.

red_flags.name: Sonia Delhon
red_flags.description: Her rapid-fire suggestions for activities and immediate excitement for food could unintentionally steamroll less assertive group members who might prefer a slower pace.

red_flags.name: Jennifer Jolly
red_flags.description: Her quick shifts in plans ('Change of plans,' 'Aquatic centre in the afternoon') indicate a spontaneity that, while fun, might make it hard for others to keep up with the evolving itinerary.

red_flags.name: Shawn Kanungo
red_flags.description: His playful jabs ('fix it to Montenegro,' 'molly kicks in') and constant search for the 'after after party' reveal a desire to keep the energy high, even if it means disrupting more sedate plans.

red_flags.name: Jeff Leong
red_flags.description: His persistent invitations for hikes, even amidst discussions of indoor pools and meal plans, suggests a singular focus on his preferred activities, sometimes missing the group's current mood.

red_flags.name: Tessa Leong
red_flags.description: Her willingness to accommodate everyone ('Sure, we‚Äôre good with wherever') might mean she rarely voices her own strong preferences, potentially leading to unmet desires.

red_flags.name: Nazia Shaikh
red_flags.description: Her complete silence in the chat, despite being a named participant, means she's either incredibly low-maintenance or secretly judging all the chaos from afar.

red_flags.name: Fahad Shaikh
red_flags.description: His total absence of messages makes one wonder if he's even aware he's in a group chat, or if he just delegates all communication duties to his travel companions.

movie_match.reason: This group's dynamic, with various personalities (and kids!) trying to navigate a shared trip, perfectly mirrors the film's concept of different emotions and perspectives working together to steer an experience, complete with moments of joy, frustration, and unexpected turns.
